Example 7 — Quarterly Variance
-----------------------------------------------------
User Question:
What is the revenue variance between 1+11 and 2+10 by quarter for FY26?

Logical Steps:
step1 = Filter FY26, l7_account = 'Revenue'.
step2 = Derive quarter from month using CASE WHEN.
step3 = Pivot versions using CASE WHEN.
step4 = Group by derived quarter. Sort chronologically Q1-Q4.

SQL:
SELECT
    CASE WHEN "month" IN ('Jan','Feb','Mar') THEN 'Q1'
         WHEN "month" IN ('Apr','May','Jun') THEN 'Q2'
         WHEN "month" IN ('Jul','Aug','Sep') THEN 'Q3'
         WHEN "month" IN ('Oct','Nov','Dec') THEN 'Q4' END AS "quarter",
    ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "latest",
    ROUND((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "previous",
    ROUND(((SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END)-SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END))/1000000.0)::numeric,2) AS "variance"
FROM finance.forecast_data_new
WHERE "Year"=2026 AND "l7_account"='Revenue'
GROUP BY CASE WHEN "month" IN ('Jan','Feb','Mar') THEN 'Q1'
              WHEN "month" IN ('Apr','May','Jun') THEN 'Q2'
              WHEN "month" IN ('Jul','Aug','Sep') THEN 'Q3'
              WHEN "month" IN ('Oct','Nov','Dec') THEN 'Q4' END
ORDER BY CASE CASE WHEN "month" IN ('Jan','Feb','Mar') THEN 'Q1'
                   WHEN "month" IN ('Apr','May','Jun') THEN 'Q2'
                   WHEN "month" IN ('Jul','Aug','Sep') THEN 'Q3'
                   WHEN "month" IN ('Oct','Nov','Dec') THEN 'Q4' END
    WHEN 'Q1' THEN 1 WHEN 'Q2' THEN 2 WHEN 'Q3' THEN 3 WHEN 'Q4' THEN 4 END;

